The paper discusses the modeling and evaluation of dynamic architectures in Systems-of-Systems (SoS), which involves collaboration between independent Constituent Systems (CSs). This topic is relevant to several sub-categories, including software engineering (cs.SE), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), systems and control (cs.SY), programming languages (cs.PL), and architecture (cs.AR). However, since the paper focuses on the modeling and evaluation of SoS architectures, cs.SE and cs.DC are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.PL, and cs.AR.
